									Laurence Parsons on March 19, 2014
									                                

                                
									Reply ‚Üì                                


                            When you say ‚ÄúStealing from another player is twice as effective‚Äù, this is only true of two-player games. It may not be the case in multiplayer. Stealing 3 from the player in last place might not be as good as gaining 5 from the game; but this in turn might not be as good as stealing 3 from the leading player. In multiplayer games, this becomes a real decision again.

                        
                    
                    


                
                
                
                        
                        
							
                        
                    
                    
                    
                        
                            
