                            As a game design novice, I found curious this comment in Game Design for Dummies:
No Roll and Move
Unless you have a time machine and are travelling back to the 1980‚Äôs to design games before anyone knew better, don‚Äôt use a single roll of the die to determine movement in your game. It‚Äôs frustrating to the players and uninspiring design. More importantly most people in the hobby game industry market will not buy your game if they see this.
The game I am designing needs to move players similar to Monopoly via the roll of dice to determine where they will land to meet their individual fate. If I don‚Äôt use dice what other random format is possible?

                        
                    
                    


                
                
                        
                        
							
                        
                    
                    
                    
                        
                            
									James Mathe on July 26, 2017
									                                

                                
									Reply ‚Üì                                


                            First off, you should really rethink why you have random movement. Is it a kids game? Why are there no choices in your movement?  If you must have random movement then maybe try something like a deck of cards where they have a hand to play movement cards from or an action point system to spend points on movement. Something to help give the player agency. No one likes winning or losing or being screwed over by just random dice rolls. A move to land on a space to take an action also makes for a VERY boring of a game.

                        
                    
                    


                

                
                
                        
                        
							
                        
                    
                    
                    
                        
                            
